# Get Class At

Retrieves the class information from the provider with the given contract address.

## Parameters

- `ctx` - The context of the request.
- `contractAddress` - The address of the contract
- `blockID` - The block identifier. Can be:
  - `BlockHash` - The hash of the block.
  - `BlockNumber` - The number of the block.
  - `"latest"` for the latest block
  - `"pending"` for the pending block

## Returns

- `ClassOutput` - The output of the class. 
- `error` - An error if any occurred.

## Example

```go
package main

import (
	"context"
	"fmt"
	"log"

	"github.com/NethermindEth/starknet.go/rpc"
	"github.com/NethermindEth/starknet.go/utils"

	"encoding/json"
)

func main() {
	rpcUrl := "https://free-rpc.nethermind.io/mainnet-juno/"
	provider, err := rpc.NewProvider(rpcUrl)
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}

	contractAddress, _ := utils.HexToFelt("0x124aeb495b947201f5fac96fd1138e326ad86195b98df6dec9009158a533b49")
	result, err := provider.ClassAt(context.Background(), rpc.BlockID{Tag: "latest"}, contractAddress)
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}
	resultJson, err := json.MarshalIndent(result, "", "  ")
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}
	fmt.Println("ClassOutput:", string(resultJson))
}
```
